# HTML :- Hyper Text Markup Language

- It is a **Markup Language** used to create the structure of a webpage.
- It is about **starting (opening) tags** and **ending (closing) tags**.
- Tags are used to mark content and tell the browser what that content represents.

## Structure

- It has a **Head portion** and **Body portion**.
    
    - **Head** contains metadata (information about the webpage itself).
        - Common tags: `meta`, `title`, `link`, `script`, etc.
    
    - **Body** contains the overall web structure and content visible to the user.
        - Common tags: Heading tags (`h1` to `h6`), Paragraph tag (`p`), Anchor tag (`a`), Image tag (`img`), etc.

- It has a `DOCTYPE` declaration and an `html` tag which contains both the `head` and `body` tags.
